#### link

Creates a link to the filtered resource.

Given study is a `StudyDrop` for a study with id `1`, the usage could look like:

<p class="code-label">Input</p>
{% raw %}
``` liquid
{{ test_study | link }}
```
{% endraw %}

<p class="code-label">Output (HTML)</p>
``` text
{{ test_study | link }}
```
<p class="code-label">Output (Rendered)</p>
<p class="html-output">
{{ test_study | link }}
</p>

You can pass a link text as argument.

<p class="code-label">Input</p>
{% raw %}
``` liquid
{{ test_study | link: 'Open in ERICA' }}
```
{% endraw %}

<p class="code-label">Output (HTML)</p>
``` text
{{ test_study | link: 'Open in ERICA' }}
```
<p class="code-label">Output (Rendered)</p>
<p class="html-output">
{{ test_study | link: 'Open in ERICA' }}
</p>

With liquid it is also easy to use a resources attribute as name for the link: 

<p class="code-label">Input</p>
{% raw %}
``` liquid
{{ test_study | link: test_study.name }}
```
{% endraw %}

<p class="code-label">Output (HTML)</p>
``` text
{{ test_study | link: test_study.name }}
```
<p class="code-label">Output (Rendered)</p>
<p class="html-output">
{{ test_study | link: test_study.name }}
</p>

